HEADWORD: Ridgeling
<hw>Ridge"ling</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Prov. E.
<ets>riggilt</ets>, <ets>riggot</ets>, ananimal half castrated, a sheep
having only one testicle; cf. Prov. G. <ets>rigel</ets>, <ets>rig</ets>,
a barrow hog, <ets>rigler</ets> a cock half castrated.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A half-castrated male animal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

